query:
CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS `ab_tests` (
  `id` int NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT,
  `accountId` int NOT NULL,
  `performanceGroupId` int DEFAULT NULL,
  `testName` varchar(255) NOT NULL,
  `testDescription` text,
  `testType` varchar(50) NOT NULL DEFAULT 'bid_optimization',
  `status` varchar(50) NOT NULL DEFAULT 'draft',
  `startDate` datetime DEFAULT NULL,
  `endDate` datetime DEFAULT NULL,
  `targetMetric` varchar(50) NOT NULL DEFAULT 'acos',
  `minSampleSize` int NOT NULL DEFAULT 100,
  `confidenceLevel` decimal(5,2) NOT NULL DEFAULT 0.95,
  `createdAt` datetime NOT NULL DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
  `updatedAt` datetime NOT NULL DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP ON UPDATE CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
  `createdBy` int DEFAULT NULL,
  PRIMARY KEY (`id`),
  KEY `idx_ab_tests_accountId` (`accountId`),
  KEY `idx_ab_tests_status` (`status`)
) ENGINE=InnoDB DEFAULT CHARSET=utf8mb4;
